parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag clock spring can cause the airbag light to stay on, the horn to malfunction, and the cruise control to fail, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The airbag light stays on or blinks intermittently
the horn does not work or only works sometimes
the cruise control does not work
the driver's seat and passenger seat collapse backward
and the airbags fail to deploy in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag does not deploy in the event of a crash
the driver's seat and passenger seat collapse backward
and the vehicle is involved in a collision.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the horn can lead to accidents or near-misses, as the driver is unable to alert other drivers or pedestrians.
symptoms: The horn does not work or only works sometimes
and the airbag light stays on or blinks intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the serpentine belt can cause the loss of power steering, alternator, and air conditioning functions, leading to a loss of vehicle control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The serpentine belt comes off the pulley
causing the power steering to fail
the alternator to stop charging
and the air conditioning to malfunction. The vehicle may stall or become difficult to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of vehicle control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
causing the vehicle to jerk or stall. The transmission may also leak fluid or produce unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of vehicle control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The engine produces unusual noises
overheats
or stalls. The engine may also leak oil or produce excessive smoke.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of vehicle control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical system malfunctions
causing the engine light to come on or the vehicle to stall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle won't shift into gear
the vehicle loses power
the transmission fluid leaks
the vehicle vibrates excessively
the speedometer malfunctions
the transmission makes unusual noises
the vehicle is unable to move forward or reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torque converter can cause the transmission to slip or hesitate, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle won't shift into gear
the vehicle loses power
the transmission fluid leaks
the vehicle vibrates excessively
the speedometer malfunctions
the transmission makes unusual noises
the vehicle is unable to move forward or reverse.
